[1] GPEI update: 3 Mar 2021
Date: Wed 3 Mar 2021
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus weekly update, as of 3 Mar 2021, WHO
-----------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week
- AFP cases: 0
- Environment: 3
- Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
- AFP cases: 12
- Environment: 26
- Others: 3

Summary of new WPV and cVDPV this week (AFP [acute flaccid paralysis] cases and ES [environmental sample] positives):
- Afghanistan: 1 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) case and 9 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Pakistan: 3 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) environmental samples, 3 cVDPV2 cases, and 10 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Egypt: 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Ethiopia: 1 cVDPV2 case and 1 positive environmental sample
- Liberia: 3 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- South Sudan: 7 cVDPV2 cases
- Tajikistan: 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample

Afghanistan
- No WPV1 case was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021 while the total number of 2020 cases remains at 56.
- 1 case of cVDPV2 was reported in Badghis bringing the number of 2021 cases to 6. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 305.
- 9 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported; 1 in Nangarhar and 4 each in Kandahar and Hilmand.

Pakistan
- No WPV1 case was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 84.
- 3 WPV1 positive ES were reported; 1 each in Punjab, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, and Balochistan.
- 3 cases of cVDPV2 were reported; 2 in Sindh and 1 in Punjab bringing the 2021 case count to 6. The number of 2020 cases remains at 135.
- 10 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported; 3 in Sindh, 2 in Punjab, 1 in the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Tribal Districts and 4 in Balochistan.

Angola
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Benin
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020. These cases are all linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.

Burkina Faso
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 59 cVDPV2 cases in the country. Burkina Faso is affected by different outbreaks, one linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria and one to the Savanes outbreak in Togo.

Cameroon
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 7 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020 [see section [4] below].

Central African Republic
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 4 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Chad
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 99 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020 from 3 different outbreaks.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Congo
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cote d'Ivoire
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 72.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 78.

Egypt
- 2 cVDPV2 positive ES were reported; 1 each in Kafr El Sheikh and Beni Suef bringing the 2021 ES count to 6. There was one sample reported in 2020.

Ethiopia
- One case of cVDPV2 was reported in SNNP [Southern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples' Region] bringing the total number of 2020 cases to 26.
- One cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in Addis Ababa.

Ghana
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 12 cases reported in 2020.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Guinea
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 45 cVDPV2 cases in the country all reported in 2020.

Kenya
- No cVDPV2 positive ES was reported this week. There was 1 cVDPV2 environmental sample reported in 2020 and 1 in 2021. The virus is linked to the Banadir outbreak in Somalia.

Liberia
- 3 cVDPV2 positive ES were reported in Montserrado.

Malaysia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There was 1 case in 2020.

Mali
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 38 cases reported in 2020.

Niger
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Nigeria
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 8 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Philippines
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There was 1 cVDPV2 case reported in 2020.
- No cVDPV1 case was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV1 cases in the country from 2019.

Sierra Leone
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country.

Somalia
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 14 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

South Sudan
- 7 cases of cVDPV2 were reported; 1 each in Warrap, Unity, Northern Bahr El Ghazal, and Central Equatoria and 3 in Jonglei. There are now 47 cVDPV2 cases in the country, all linked to the ongoing outbreak in Chad.

Sudan
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains 57. The initial viruses were linked to the ongoing outbreak in Chad followed by local transmission.

Tajikistan
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021 and 1 case was reported in 2020.
- One cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in Dushanbe.

Togo
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There were 9 cases reported in 2020.

Yemen
- No case of cVDPV1 was reported this week. There are 30 cVDPV1 cases reported in the country so far.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 2 Mar 2021
- Wild poliovirus (WPV)
Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 2 (compared with 17 for the same period in 2020)
Total global WPV1 cases in 2020: 140

- Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 13 (compared with 19 for the same period in 2020)
Total global cVDPV cases in 2020: 1067

--
