Poliovirus weekly update, as of 24 Feb 2021, WHO
------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
- AFP cases: 1
- Environment: 6
- Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
- AFP cases: 18
- Environment: 7
- Others: 4

Summary of new WPV and cVDPV this week (AFP cases and ES positives):
- Afghanistan: 6 cVDPV2 cases
- Pakistan: 1 WPV1 and 2 cVDPV2 cases, 6 WPV1 and f5 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Congo DR: 1 cVDPV2 case and 1 cVDPV2 positive ES
- Egypt: 1 cVDPV2 positive ES
- Ethiopia: 1 cVDPV2 case
- Guinea: 6 cVDPV2 cases
- Mali: 2 cVDPV2 cases

--
communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[After 2 years of significant WPV1 activity in Pakistan and Afghanistan, WPV1 transmission continues, but apparently at a slower pace. That being said, positive environmental samples mean that the virus is actively circulating. But, 2020 was a major year for cVDPV outbreaks with a total to date of 1067 confirmed AFP cases associated with circulating vaccine derived polioviruses and in 2021, as of 3 Mar, 13 cases have already been reported. Countries involved included Eurasia (Tajikistan), Middle East (Egypt, Yemen), Asia (Pakistan, Afghanistan, Malaysia), Africa (Angola, Benin, Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Central African Republic, Chad, Congo, Cote d'Ivoire, DR Congo, Ethiopia, Ghana, Guinea, Kenya, Liberia, Mali, Niger, Nigeria, Sierra Leone, Somalia. South Sudan, Sudan, Togo), and the Pacific (Philippines).

See Dr T Jacob John's comment re: vaccine derived poliovirus cases and estimated size of the outbreaks below.

For a global map showing distribution of the poliovirus outbreaks during the past 12 months (both WPV1 and cVDPV associated, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. - Mod.MPP]

